The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Indiabulls clears air on tax trip

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Oct. 26: Indiabulls Financial Services today confirmed that that the income tax (I-T) department had visited three of its offices under a survey operation for third-party verifications.

 The income tax survey was related to collection of transactions and verification details of clients of Indiabulls Securities, who have dealt in penny stocks. Indiabulls Securities is one of the nine subsidiaries of the company.

 Most of such client accounts have been shut down by Indiabulls Securities as part of its internal due diligence and compliance process. 

 The company has clarified the visit of the I-T department was not related to any firms of the Indiabulls group and was limited to client details of Indiabulls Securities. The group has paid approximately Rs 36 crore in income tax for the first six months of this fiscal. 

 Indiabulls Securities has 129 offices across the country. It is one of the fastest growing stock brokerages and a bulk of its deals are transacted online. 




